{"title":"Pro bike: Tadej Pogačar’s Tour of Flanders Colnago V4Rs","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-tour-of-flanders-colnago-v4rs","date":1744037278000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-tour-of-flanders-colnago-v4rs\">Pro bike: Tadej Pogačar’s Tour of Flanders Colnago V4Rs</a></p>\n\n<p>Yes, it’s confirmed: Tadej Pogačar is very good at riding his bike. He won his eighth Monument and second Tour of Flanders this weekend in style, and was riding this, the Colnago V4Rs.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While Pogačar has been spotted in the wild on what looks to be the V5Rs, he’s still racing the V4Rs for now and is giving it a pretty solid send-off. Assuming he transitions to the new bike for the Tour de France (and probably the Dauphiné) and rides the Y1Rs aero bike at Paris-Roubaix this week, Flanders would’ve been one of his last race days on this bike before it gets put out to pasture after the Ardennes Classics.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Photographer Xavier Pereyron got in amongst it in Belgium on Sunday to get a closer look (and it’s pretty much identical to <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-strade-bianche-colnago-v4rs-2025\">what he rode at Strade Bianche</a>).</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Tadej Pogačar Tour of Flanders 2025 Colnago V4Rs spec</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bar tape: </strong>Colnago</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bottle cages: </strong>Elite Leggero Carbon</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Bottles: </strong>Elite Fly</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Chainrings: </strong>Carbon-Ti custom, 54/40t</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Computer: </strong>Wahoo Elemnt Bolt</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Computer mount: </strong>K-Edge</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Groupset: </strong>Shimano Dura-Ace Di2, 165mm cranks</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Handlebar/stem:</strong> Enve SES Aero Pro</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Pedals:</strong> Shimano Dura-Ace</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Power meter: </strong>Shimano Dura-Ace</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Saddle:</strong> Fizik Argo Adaptive</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tyres: </strong>Continental Grand Prix 5000 S TR 30mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Wheels: </strong>Enve SES 4.5</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+2\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-2-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Cyclist-Bikes-Gallery-Ronde-Van-Vlaanderen-06-avril-2025-76-970x647.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Cyclist-Bikes-Gallery-Ronde-Van-Vlaanderen-06-avril-2025-76-970x646.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Cyclist-Bikes-Gallery-Ronde-Van-Vlaanderen-06-avril-2025-76-300x200.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/04/Cyclist-Bikes-Gallery-Ronde-Van-Vlaander